Order Instructions

Client Order Instructions:

Kind Lending Client Order Instructions

 

Best Contact for Order Escalations - AppraisalSupport@KindLending.com

 

Integration

  • Platform: Closing Corp
  • Submit to UCDP/EAD: Enabled on Fastapps side (set to generate automatically)
  • Borrower Report Delivery: Not enabled on Fastapps side.
  • ACE + PDR Orders: UPD (bACE) connection established so we can process these for them.

 

Fees & Payment

Fee Schedule: Kind uses its own fee schedule, which will populate automatically from Closing Corp.  CLICK HERE TO SEE THE FEES

Payment Handling

  • DO NOT send Fastapp payment links.
  • All payment is handled exclusively through the Closing Corp system.

Payment Process

  • Brokers place a credit card on file in Closing Corp, or the platform sends a payment link to the borrower.
  • Once payment is made, a payment message will appear showing funds have been collected.  Proceed once you see payment collection.
  • Payment must be received before assignment, unless approval is granted by Vendor Support or one of the following managers:
    • April Perrine
    • Chrissy Murphy
    • Natalie Cooke
    • Delfino Aguilar

 

Fee Modifications & Upcharges

  • Use the Fee Modification Tool in ValueLink for any fee changes or upcharges.
  • The client must accept or decline the fee change through their platform.
  • Once accepted, a payment link will trigger on their end.
  • Wait until the Payment Received message appears in our system before proceeding.
  • Ensure the invoice reflects the updated balance so Kind can process payment promptly.

 

Cancelled Orders

Cancelled Orders with No Refund Needed

  • Brokers may request cancellations directly.
  • If the cancellation seems questionable, confirm with VendorSupport@KindLending.com.
  • Send a message to Michelle Perez requesting a fee adjustment in Closing Corp to set the fee to $0.

Cancelled Orders Requiring Refunds

  • Brokers may request cancellations directly.
  • Confirm with VendorSupport@KindLending.com if uncertain.
  • Email Michelle Perez to request the refund.
  • Note: This integration does not support refunds in ValueLink.
  • Michelle will:
    1. Process the refund through Fastapps merchant account, and
    2. Adjust the fee in Closing Corp accordingly.

 

Reactivating a Cancelled Order

If the client wants to reactivate a cancelled order, they must place a brand new order.
Reactivations cannot be processed due to integration limitations.

 

Revision Requests

Process revisions immediately if the request comes from any of the following:

  • Underwriter (UW)
  • Appraisal Underwriter (Appraisal UW)
  • Kind Lending Appraisal Team
  • KL Vendor Support

Example of a valid message: Message from the Appraisal Review Team   CLICK HERE FOR EXAMPLE

If the revision is submitted by a broker or any other Kind Lending team member not listed above, confirm with VendorSupport@KindLending.com before proceeding.

 

Reconsideration of Value (ROV)

  • Brokers cannot submit ROVs directly to Fastapp.
  • ROV requests must come from the Kind Appraisal Review Team.
  • Respond to brokers with:

Hello reconsiderations of value must be requested by the Kind Appraisal Review Team. Please contact them at VendorSupport@KindLending.com.

Valid ROV requests must include this note:

We have received a reconsideration of value request. Please have the appraiser review the suggested sales to determine if they are suitable comparables. If they are not, please have the appraiser address this within the report. The reconsideration of value form has been uploaded. This request has been submitted from the Kind Lending Appraisal Review Team.
